But this was just the stickynotes. In this particular world piecespace, there were also paperclips everywhere. A rainbow of different colors, clipped to things, a few bent into peculiar shapes. Some were clipped to clothing, many on hats, many on pockets. A large number of paperclips were attached to the neighboring system of stickynotes, too. There were a few paper stacks with colored paperclips binding everything together. The paperclips were a lot more versatile than stickynotes, more durable especially, but they were less spacious and lacked the ability to store nonbrain data. They were however, very good at storing memories in colored chains, many dangling throughout the interior residence space (and a few short ones dangling in the transport space.

